{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1142,"text":"I need to make a confession\nat the outset here."},{"time":3682,"text":"A little over 20 years ago,\nI did something that I regret,"},{"time":9511,"text":"something that I'm not\nparticularly proud of."},{"time":12881,"text":"Something that, in many ways,\nI wish no one would ever know,"},{"time":16280,"text":"but here I feel kind of obliged to reveal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19563,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":21840,"text":"In the late 1980s,"},{"time":23888,"text":"in a moment of youthful indiscretion,"},{"time":27307,"text":"I went to law school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28832,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":33506,"text":"In America, law is a professional degree:"},{"time":35967,"text":"after your university degree,\nyou go on to law school."},{"time":38696,"text":"When I got to law school,"},{"time":40973,"text":"I didn't do very well."},{"time":43583,"text":"To put it mildly, I didn't do very well."},{"time":45528,"text":"I, in fact, graduated in the part\nof my law school class"},{"time":48559,"text":"that made the top 90% possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":58825,"text":"I never practiced law a day in my life;"},{"time":62404,"text":"I pretty much wasn't allowed to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64412,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":67150,"text":"But today, against my better judgment,"},{"time":70655,"text":"against the advice of my own wife,"},{"time":73000,"text":"I want to try to dust off\nsome of those legal skills --"},{"time":77000,"text":"what's left of those legal skills."},{"time":79383,"text":"I don't want to tell you a story."},{"time":82000,"text":"I want to make a case."},{"time":84388,"text":"I want to make a hard-headed,"},{"time":86778,"text":"evidence-based,"},{"time":88000,"text":"dare I say lawyerly case,"},{"time":91198,"text":"for rethinking how we run our businesses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95793,"text":"So, ladies and gentlemen of the jury,"},{"time":97802,"text":"take a look at this."},{"time":99269,"text":"This is called the candle problem."},{"time":101600,"text":"Some of you might know it."},{"time":103298,"text":"It's created in 1945"},{"time":105000,"text":"by a psychologist named Karl Duncker."},{"time":107000,"text":"He created this experiment"},{"time":109000,"text":"that is used in many other experiments\nin behavioral science."},{"time":112155,"text":"And here's how it works.\nSuppose I'm the experimenter."},{"time":115000,"text":"I bring you into a room."},{"time":116644,"text":"I give you a candle,\nsome thumbtacks and some matches."},{"time":120892,"text":"And I say to you,"},{"time":121987,"text":"\"Your job is to attach\nthe candle to the wall"},{"time":125000,"text":"so the wax doesn't drip onto the table.\""},{"time":128150,"text":"Now what would you do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":129709,"text":"Many people begin trying\nto thumbtack the candle to the wall."},{"time":133328,"text":"Doesn't work."},{"time":134690,"text":"I saw somebody\nkind of make the motion over here --"},{"time":139444,"text":"some people have a great idea\nwhere they light the match,"},{"time":142572,"text":"melt the side of the candle,\ntry to adhere it to the wall."},{"time":145525,"text":"It's an awesome idea. Doesn't work."},{"time":148667,"text":"And eventually, after five or ten minutes,"},{"time":151000,"text":"most people figure out the solution,"},{"time":153000,"text":"which you can see here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154769,"text":"The key is to overcome\nwhat's called functional fixedness."},{"time":158583,"text":"You look at that box and you see it\nonly as a receptacle for the tacks."},{"time":162571,"text":"But it can also have this other function,"},{"time":164601,"text":"as a platform for the candle."},{"time":166887,"text":"The candle problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168000,"text":"I want to tell you about an experiment\nusing the candle problem,"},{"time":171995,"text":"done by a scientist named Sam Glucksberg,"},{"time":174478,"text":"who is now at Princeton University, US,"},{"time":176623,"text":"This shows the power of incentives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180000,"text":"He gathered his participants and said:"},{"time":182000,"text":"\"I'm going to time you, how quickly\nyou can solve this problem.\""},{"time":185849,"text":"To one group he said,"},{"time":187349,"text":"\"I'm going to time you to establish norms,"},{"time":190000,"text":"averages for how long it typically takes\nsomeone to solve this sort of problem.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":194565,"text":"To the second group he offered rewards."},{"time":197000,"text":"He said, \"If you're in the top 25%\nof the fastest times,"},{"time":201747,"text":"you get five dollars."},{"time":203714,"text":"If you're the fastest of everyone\nwe're testing here today,"},{"time":207491,"text":"you get 20 dollars.\""},{"time":209000,"text":"Now this is several years ago,\nadjusted for inflation,"},{"time":211907,"text":"it's a decent sum of money\nfor a few minutes of work."},{"time":214476,"text":"It's a nice motivator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216000,"text":"Question:"},{"time":217167,"text":"How much faster did this group\nsolve the problem?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":221377,"text":"Answer:"},{"time":222647,"text":"It took them, on average,\nthree and a half minutes longer."},{"time":228313,"text":"3.5 min longer."},{"time":229552,"text":"This makes no sense, right?"},{"time":231398,"text":"I mean, I'm an American.\nI believe in free markets."},{"time":234525,"text":"That's not how it's supposed\nto work, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":238208,"text":"If you want people to perform better,\nyou reward them. Right?"},{"time":242147,"text":"Bonuses, commissions,\ntheir own reality show."},{"time":245000,"text":"Incentivize them."},{"time":247862,"text":"That's how business works."},{"time":249269,"text":"But that's not happening here."},{"time":251306,"text":"You've got an incentive designed"},{"time":253000,"text":"to sharpen thinking\nand accelerate creativity,"},{"time":256820,"text":"and it does just the opposite."},{"time":259000,"text":"It dulls thinking and blocks creativity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262000,"text":"What's interesting about this experiment"},{"time":263955,"text":"is that it's not an aberration."},{"time":265549,"text":"This has been replicated\nover and over again"},{"time":268658,"text":"for nearly 40 years."},{"time":271700,"text":"These contingent motivators --"},{"time":274000,"text":"if you do this, then you get that --"},{"time":276398,"text":"work in some circumstances."},{"time":278000,"text":"But for a lot of tasks,\nthey actually either don't work"},{"time":281836,"text":"or, often, they do harm."},{"time":284688,"text":"This is one of the most robust findings\nin social science,"},{"time":290785,"text":"and also one of the most ignored."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293158,"text":"I spent the last couple of years"},{"time":294772,"text":"looking at the science\nof human motivation,"},{"time":296867,"text":"particularly the dynamics\nof extrinsic motivators"},{"time":299253,"text":"and intrinsic motivators."},{"time":301000,"text":"And I'm telling you, it's not even close."},{"time":303436,"text":"If you look at the science,\nthere is a mismatch"},{"time":305798,"text":"between what science knows"},{"time":307675,"text":"and what business does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309110,"text":"What's alarming here\nis that our business operating system --"},{"time":312380,"text":"think of the set of assumptions\nand protocols beneath our businesses,"},{"time":315712,"text":"how we motivate people,\nhow we apply our human resources--"},{"time":320470,"text":"it's built entirely\naround these extrinsic motivators,"},{"time":323724,"text":"around carrots and sticks."},{"time":325319,"text":"That's actually fine for many kinds\nof 20th century tasks."},{"time":329532,"text":"But for 21st century tasks,"},{"time":331667,"text":"that mechanistic,\nreward-and-punishment approach"},{"time":335222,"text":"doesn't work,"},{"time":336914,"text":"often doesn't work,"},{"time":338420,"text":"and often does harm."},{"time":339615,"text":"Let me show you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340822,"text":"Glucksberg did another similar experiment,"},{"time":343923,"text":"he presented the problem\nin a slightly different way,"},{"time":346560,"text":"like this up here."},{"time":348502,"text":"Attach the candle to the wall\nso the wax doesn't drip onto the table."},{"time":351803,"text":"Same deal. You: we're timing for norms."},{"time":354303,"text":"You: we're incentivizing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356769,"text":"What happened this time?"},{"time":359200,"text":"This time, the incentivized group\nkicked the other group's butt."},{"time":365428,"text":"Why?"},{"time":367254,"text":"Because when the tacks are out of the box,"},{"time":369785,"text":"it's pretty easy isn't it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":373261,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":375735,"text":"If-then rewards work really well\nfor those sorts of tasks,"},{"time":380737,"text":"where there is a simple set of rules"},{"time":382477,"text":"and a clear destination to go to."},{"time":385000,"text":"Rewards, by their very nature,"},{"time":387000,"text":"narrow our focus, concentrate the mind;"},{"time":389000,"text":"that's why they work in so many cases."},{"time":391359,"text":"So, for tasks like this,"},{"time":393462,"text":"a narrow focus, where you just see\nthe goal right there,"},{"time":396839,"text":"zoom straight ahead to it,"},{"time":398243,"text":"they work really well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399896,"text":"But for the real candle problem,"},{"time":402640,"text":"you don't want to be looking like this."},{"time":404656,"text":"The solution is on the periphery.\nYou want to be looking around."},{"time":407810,"text":"That reward actually narrows our focus"},{"time":410461,"text":"and restricts our possibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412000,"text":"Let me tell you why this is so important."},{"time":415176,"text":"In western Europe,"},{"time":418303,"text":"in many parts of Asia,"},{"time":419412,"text":"in North America, in Australia,"},{"time":422211,"text":"white-collar workers are doing\nless of this kind of work,"},{"time":425801,"text":"and more of this kind of work."},{"time":429865,"text":"That routine, rule-based,\nleft-brain work --"},{"time":432860,"text":"certain kinds of accounting,\nfinancial analysis,"},{"time":435600,"text":"computer programming --"},{"time":437319,"text":"has become fairly easy to outsource,"},{"time":439538,"text":"fairly easy to automate."},{"time":441593,"text":"Software can do it faster."},{"time":443793,"text":"Low-cost providers can do it cheaper."},{"time":446142,"text":"So what really matters"},{"time":449134,"text":"are the more right-brained\ncreative, conceptual kinds of abilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453786,"text":"Think about your own work."},{"time":456191,"text":"Think about your own work."},{"time":458873,"text":"Are the problems that you face,"},{"time":460479,"text":"or even the problems\nwe've been talking about here,"},{"time":463000,"text":"do they have a clear set of rules,"},{"time":465912,"text":"and a single solution?"},{"time":467523,"text":"No. The rules are mystifying."},{"time":470000,"text":"The solution, if it exists at all,"},{"time":472270,"text":"is surprising and not obvious."},{"time":475000,"text":"Everybody in this room"},{"time":477778,"text":"is dealing with their own version\nof the candle problem."},{"time":482000,"text":"And for candle problems of any kind,"},{"time":485161,"text":"in any field,"},{"time":486855,"text":"those if-then rewards,"},{"time":489872,"text":"the things around which we've built\nso many of our businesses,"},{"time":494138,"text":"don't work!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":495995,"text":"It makes me crazy."},{"time":498475,"text":"And here's the thing."},{"time":500435,"text":"This is not a feeling."},{"time":503696,"text":"Okay? I'm a lawyer;\nI don't believe in feelings."},{"time":506814,"text":"This is not a philosophy."},{"time":510481,"text":"I'm an American;\nI don't believe in philosophy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512767,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":515365,"text":"This is a fact --"},{"time":518357,"text":"or, as we say in my hometown\nof Washington, D.C.,"},{"time":520825,"text":"a true fact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522439,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":524907,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":528725,"text":"Let me give you an example."},{"time":530391,"text":"Let me marshal the evidence here."},{"time":532000,"text":"I'm not telling a story,\nI'm making a case."},{"time":534137,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen\nof the jury, some evidence:"},{"time":536432,"text":"Dan Ariely, one of the great\neconomists of our time,"},{"time":539831,"text":"he and three colleagues\ndid a study of some MIT students."},{"time":543326,"text":"They gave these MIT\nstudents a bunch of games,"},{"time":546000,"text":"games that involved creativity,"},{"time":548000,"text":"and motor skills, and concentration."},{"time":550302,"text":"And the offered them, for performance,"},{"time":552407,"text":"three levels of rewards:"},{"time":554445,"text":"small reward, medium reward,\nlarge reward."},{"time":558715,"text":"If you do really well\nyou get the large reward, on down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562876,"text":"What happened?"},{"time":564234,"text":"As long as the task\ninvolved only mechanical skill"},{"time":567000,"text":"bonuses worked as they would be expected:"},{"time":569000,"text":"the higher the pay,\nthe better the performance."},{"time":572721,"text":"Okay?"},{"time":573896,"text":"But once the task called\nfor even rudimentary cognitive skill,"},{"time":579000,"text":"a larger reward led to poorer performance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585096,"text":"Then they said,"},{"time":586270,"text":"\"Let's see if there's any\ncultural bias here."},{"time":588429,"text":"Let's go to Madurai, India and test it.\""},{"time":590406,"text":"Standard of living is lower."},{"time":592000,"text":"In Madurai, a reward that is modest\nin North American standards,"},{"time":595501,"text":"is more meaningful there."},{"time":597699,"text":"Same deal. A bunch of games,\nthree levels of rewards."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601125,"text":"What happens?"},{"time":603141,"text":"People offered the medium level of rewards"},{"time":606165,"text":"did no better than people\noffered the small rewards."},{"time":608769,"text":"But this time,\npeople offered the highest rewards,"},{"time":613272,"text":"they did the worst of all."},{"time":616817,"text":"In eight of the nine tasks we examined\nacross three experiments,"},{"time":620214,"text":"higher incentives led\nto worse performance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625474,"text":"Is this some kind of touchy-feely\nsocialist conspiracy going on here?"},{"time":631474,"text":"No, these are economists from MIT,"},{"time":634274,"text":"from Carnegie Mellon,\nfrom the University of Chicago."},{"time":637000,"text":"Do you know who sponsored this research?"},{"time":639645,"text":"The Federal Reserve Bank\nof the United States."},{"time":643789,"text":"That's the American experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645633,"text":"Let's go across the pond\nto the London School of Economics,"},{"time":648432,"text":"LSE, London School of Economics,"},{"time":651000,"text":"alma mater of eleven\nNobel Laureates in economics."},{"time":654468,"text":"Training ground for great\neconomic thinkers"},{"time":657000,"text":"like George Soros, and Friedrich Hayek,"},{"time":660000,"text":"and Mick Jagger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661311,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":662634,"text":"Last month,"},{"time":664428,"text":"just last month,"},{"time":665951,"text":"economists at LSE looked at 51 studies"},{"time":669000,"text":"of pay-for-performance plans,\ninside of companies."},{"time":672000,"text":"Here's what they said:"},{"time":673475,"text":"\"We find that financial incentives"},{"time":675295,"text":"can result in a negative impact\non overall performance.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":680776,"text":"There is a mismatch\nbetween what science knows"},{"time":684499,"text":"and what business does."},{"time":686000,"text":"And what worries me,\nas we stand here in the rubble"},{"time":689301,"text":"of the economic collapse,"},{"time":691000,"text":"is that too many organizations\nare making their decisions,"},{"time":695000,"text":"their policies about talent and people,"},{"time":697396,"text":"based on assumptions that are outdated,"},{"time":701547,"text":"unexamined,"},{"time":702761,"text":"and rooted more in folklore\nthan in science."},{"time":706404,"text":"And if we really want to get\nout of this economic mess,"},{"time":709000,"text":"if we really want high performance"},{"time":711117,"text":"on those definitional tasks\nof the 21st century,"},{"time":713588,"text":"the solution is not to do\nmore of the wrong things,"},{"time":719552,"text":"to entice people with a sweeter carrot,"},{"time":721899,"text":"or threaten them with a sharper stick."},{"time":724322,"text":"We need a whole new approach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"The good news is that the scientists"},{"time":728000,"text":"who've been studying motivation\nhave given us this new approach."},{"time":731212,"text":"It's built much more\naround intrinsic motivation."},{"time":734331,"text":"Around the desire to do things\nbecause they matter,"},{"time":736810,"text":"because we like it, they're interesting,\nor part of something important."},{"time":740397,"text":"And to my mind, that new operating\nsystem for our businesses"},{"time":744000,"text":"revolves around three elements:"},{"time":745725,"text":"autonomy, mastery and purpose."},{"time":749000,"text":"Autonomy: the urge\nto direct our own lives."},{"time":752000,"text":"Mastery: the desire to get better\nand better at something that matters."},{"time":756269,"text":"Purpose: the yearning to do what we do"},{"time":759000,"text":"in the service of something\nlarger than ourselves."},{"time":762217,"text":"These are the building blocks\nof an entirely new operating system"},{"time":765535,"text":"for our businesses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"I want to talk today only about autonomy."},{"time":771000,"text":"In the 20th century, we came up\nwith this idea of management."},{"time":774000,"text":"Management did not emanate from nature."},{"time":776318,"text":"Management is not a tree,\nit's a television set."},{"time":780000,"text":"Somebody invented it."},{"time":782248,"text":"It doesn't mean\nit's going to work forever."},{"time":784272,"text":"Management is great."},{"time":786303,"text":"Traditional notions\nof management are great"},{"time":788381,"text":"if you want compliance."},{"time":790000,"text":"But if you want engagement,\nself-direction works better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793207,"text":"Some examples of some kind\nof radical notions of self-direction."},{"time":797271,"text":"You don't see a lot of it,"},{"time":800231,"text":"but you see the first stirrings\nof something really interesting going on,"},{"time":803731,"text":"what it means is paying people adequately\nand fairly, absolutely --"},{"time":807398,"text":"getting the issue of money off the table,"},{"time":809707,"text":"and then giving people lots of autonomy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811706,"text":"Some examples."},{"time":813000,"text":"How many of you have heard\nof the company Atlassian?"},{"time":817468,"text":"It looks like less than half."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":820429,"text":"Atlassian is an Australian\nsoftware company."},{"time":825000,"text":"And they do something incredibly cool."},{"time":826995,"text":"A few times a year\nthey tell their engineers,"},{"time":829763,"text":"\"Go for the next 24 hours\nand work on anything you want,"},{"time":833793,"text":"as long as it's not part\nof your regular job."},{"time":835927,"text":"Work on anything you want.\""},{"time":837341,"text":"Engineers use this time to come up\nwith a cool patch for code,"},{"time":841128,"text":"come up with an elegant hack."},{"time":842594,"text":"Then they present all of the stuff\nthat they've developed"},{"time":845584,"text":"to their teammates,\nto the rest of the company,"},{"time":848328,"text":"in this wild and woolly all-hands meeting\nat the end of the day."},{"time":852304,"text":"Being Australians, everybody has a beer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854523,"text":"They call them FedEx Days."},{"time":857452,"text":"Why?"},{"time":859515,"text":"Because you have to deliver\nsomething overnight."},{"time":862817,"text":"It's pretty; not bad."},{"time":864408,"text":"It's a huge trademark violation,\nbut it's pretty clever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867100,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":868461,"text":"That one day of intense autonomy"},{"time":870163,"text":"has produced a whole array\nof software fixes"},{"time":872239,"text":"that might never have existed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874000,"text":"It's worked so well that Atlassian\nhas taken it to the next level"},{"time":877092,"text":"with 20% time --"},{"time":878174,"text":"done, famously, at Google --"},{"time":880366,"text":"where engineers can spend\n20% of their time"},{"time":882452,"text":"working on anything they want."},{"time":884421,"text":"They have autonomy over their time,"},{"time":886112,"text":"their task, their team, their technique."},{"time":888349,"text":"Radical amounts of autonomy."},{"time":890327,"text":"And at Google, as many of you know,"},{"time":894277,"text":"about half of the new products\nin a typical year"},{"time":896634,"text":"are birthed during that 20% time:"},{"time":899134,"text":"things like Gmail, Orkut, Google News."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902000,"text":"Let me give you an even more\nradical example of it:"},{"time":904944,"text":"something called the Results Only\nWork Environment (the ROWE),"},{"time":908841,"text":"created by two American consultants,"},{"time":910931,"text":"in place at a dozen companies\naround North America."},{"time":913634,"text":"In a ROWE people don't have schedules."},{"time":917568,"text":"They show up when they want."},{"time":919239,"text":"They don't have to be in the office\nat a certain time, or any time."},{"time":923317,"text":"They just have to get their work done."},{"time":925286,"text":"How they do it, when they do it,\nwhere they do it, is totally up to them."},{"time":930484,"text":"Meetings in these kinds\nof environments are optional."}]},{"cues":[{"time":934879,"text":"What happens?"},{"time":936364,"text":"Almost across the board,"},{"time":938099,"text":"productivity goes up,\nworker engagement goes up,"},{"time":941333,"text":"worker satisfaction goes up,\nturnover goes down."},{"time":945000,"text":"Autonomy, mastery and purpose,"},{"time":947000,"text":"the building blocks\nof a new way of doing things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949636,"text":"Some of you might look at this and say,"},{"time":952000,"text":"\"Hmm, that sounds nice, but it's Utopian.\""},{"time":955358,"text":"And I say, \"Nope."},{"time":958365,"text":"I have proof.\""},{"time":960478,"text":"The mid-1990s, Microsoft started\nan encyclopedia called Encarta."},{"time":964000,"text":"They had deployed\nall the right incentives,"},{"time":967341,"text":"They paid professionals\nto write and edit thousands of articles."},{"time":971214,"text":"Well-compensated managers\noversaw the whole thing"},{"time":973827,"text":"to make sure it came in\non budget and on time."},{"time":978000,"text":"A few years later,\nanother encyclopedia got started."},{"time":980528,"text":"Different model, right?"},{"time":983346,"text":"Do it for fun."},{"time":985030,"text":"No one gets paid a cent,\nor a euro or a yen."},{"time":989096,"text":"Do it because you like to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":991044,"text":"Just 10 years ago,"},{"time":993000,"text":"if you had gone to an economist, anywhere,"},{"time":995273,"text":"\"Hey, I've got these two different\nmodels for creating an encyclopedia."},{"time":998872,"text":"If they went head to head, who would win?\""},{"time":1001817,"text":"10 years ago you could not\nhave found a single sober economist"},{"time":1005407,"text":"anywhere on planet Earth"},{"time":1007651,"text":"who would have predicted\nthe Wikipedia model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1010547,"text":"This is the titanic battle\nbetween these two approaches."},{"time":1013270,"text":"This is the Ali-Frazier\nof motivation, right?"},{"time":1016362,"text":"This is the Thrilla in Manila."},{"time":1018225,"text":"Intrinsic motivators\nversus extrinsic motivators."},{"time":1021418,"text":"Autonomy, mastery and purpose,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"versus carrot and sticks, and who wins?"},{"time":1025581,"text":"Intrinsic motivation, autonomy, mastery\nand purpose, in a knockout."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029135,"text":"Let me wrap up."},{"time":1032523,"text":"There is a mismatch between\nwhat science knows and what business does."},{"time":1035850,"text":"Here is what science knows."},{"time":1037461,"text":"One: Those 20th century rewards,"},{"time":1039168,"text":"those motivators we think\nare a natural part of business,"},{"time":1042172,"text":"do work, but only in a surprisingly\nnarrow band of circumstances."},{"time":1045897,"text":"Two: Those if-then rewards\noften destroy creativity."},{"time":1050714,"text":"Three: The secret to high performance\nisn't rewards and punishments,"},{"time":1054538,"text":"but that unseen intrinsic drive--"},{"time":1056172,"text":"the drive to do things for their own sake."},{"time":1059000,"text":"The drive to do things cause they matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1061000,"text":"And here's the best part."},{"time":1063000,"text":"We already know this."},{"time":1064244,"text":"The science confirms\nwhat we know in our hearts."},{"time":1066818,"text":"So, if we repair this mismatch\nbetween science and business,"},{"time":1071672,"text":"if we bring our motivation,\nnotions of motivation"},{"time":1074629,"text":"into the 21st century,"},{"time":1076380,"text":"if we get past this lazy,\ndangerous, ideology"},{"time":1080418,"text":"of carrots and sticks,"},{"time":1082474,"text":"we can strengthen our businesses,"},{"time":1085227,"text":"we can solve a lot\nof those candle problems,"},{"time":1087833,"text":"and maybe, maybe --"},{"time":1092000,"text":"we can change the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1093777,"text":"I rest my case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1095106,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}